类 GetObjectRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.aliyun.oss.model.WebServiceRequest

  • 直接已知子类:
    SelectObjectRequest

    public class GetObjectRequest
extends GenericRequest
    This is the request class that is used to download an object from OSS. It wraps all the information needed to download an object.

    • 方法详细资料

      • getRange

        public long[] getRange()
        Gets the range of the object to download. The range is in the form of {start, end}---start and end is position of the object's content.
        返回:
        The range of the object to download.

      • setRange

        public void setRange(long start,
            long end)
        Sets the range of the object to download (optional).
        参数:
        start -

        Start position

        When the start is non-negative, it means the starting position to download. When the start is -1, it means the range is determined by the end only and the end could not be -1. For example, when start is -1 and end is 100. It means the download range will be the last 100 bytes.

        end -

        End position

        When the end is non-negative, it means the ending position to download. When the end is -1, it means the range is determined by the start only and the start could not be -1. For example, when end is -1 and start is 100. It means the download range will be all exception first 100 bytes.

      • withRange

        public GetObjectRequest withRange(long start,
                         long end)
        Sets the range of the object to download and return current GetObjectRequest instance (this).
        参数:
        start -

        Start position

        When the start is non-negative, it means the starting position to download. When the start is -1, it means the range is determined by the end only and the end could not be -1. For example, when start is -1 and end is 100. It means the download range will be the last 100 bytes.

        end -

        End position

        When the end is non-negative, it means the ending position to download. When the end is -1, it means the range is determined by the start only and the start could not be -1. For example, when end is -1 and start is 100. It means the download range will be all exception first 100 bytes.

      • getMatchingETagConstraints

        public List<String> getMatchingETagConstraints()
        Gets the matching Etag constraints. If the first ETag returned matches the object's ETag, the file would be downloaded. Currently OSS only supports one ETag. Otherwise, return precondition failure (412).
        返回:
        The list of expected ETags.

      • setMatchingETagConstraints

        public void setMatchingETagConstraints(List<String> eTagList)
        Sets the matching Etag constraints. If the first ETag returned matches the object's ETag, the file would be downloaded. Otherwise, return precondition failure (412).
        参数:
        eTagList - The expected ETag list. OSS only supports one ETag.

      • clearMatchingETagConstraints

        public void clearMatchingETagConstraints()

      • getNonmatchingETagConstraints

        public List<String> getNonmatchingETagConstraints()
        Gets the non-matching Etag constraints. If the first ETag returned does not match the object's ETag, the file would be downloaded. Currently OSS only supports one ETag. Otherwise, return precondition failure (412).
        返回:
        The list of expected ETags (only the first one matters though).

      • setNonmatchingETagConstraints

        public void setNonmatchingETagConstraints(List<String> eTagList)
        Sets the non-matching Etag constraints. If the first ETag returned does not match the object's ETag, the file would be downloaded. Currently OSS only supports one ETag. Otherwise, returns precondition failure (412).
        参数:
        eTagList - The list of expected ETags (only the first one matters though).

      • getUnmodifiedSinceConstraint

        public Date getUnmodifiedSinceConstraint()
        Gets the unmodified since constraints. If the timestamp returned is equal or later than the actual file's modified time, the file would be downloaded. Otherwise, the download API returns precondition failure (412).
        返回:
        The timestamp.

      • setUnmodifiedSinceConstraint

        public void setUnmodifiedSinceConstraint(Date date)
        Sets the unmodified since constraints. If the timestamp specified in date parameter is equal or later than the actual file's modified time, the file would be downloaded. Otherwise, the download API returns precondition failure (412).
        参数:
        date - The timestamp.

      • getModifiedSinceConstraint

        public Date getModifiedSinceConstraint()
        Gets the modified since constraints. If the timestamp returned is earlier than the actual file's modified time, the file would be downloaded. Otherwise, the download API returns precondition failure (412).
        返回:
        “If-Modified-Since” timestamp.

      • setModifiedSinceConstraint

        public void setModifiedSinceConstraint(Date date)
        Sets the modified since constraints. If the timestamp returned is earlier than the actual file's modified time, the file would be downloaded. Otherwise, the download API returns precondition failure (412).
        参数:
        date - “If-Modified-Since” parameter.
